<doc id="1051272" wikidata="Q7081896" url="?curid=1051272" title="Okeechobee station (Metrorail)">
<text>Okeechobee station is a Metrorail station in Hialeah, Florida. The station is located at the intersection of West 20th Street and Okeechobee Road (US 27), one block south of the Hialeah Expressway (SR 934). It opened to passenger service on May 19, 1985, and was previously the northwestern terminus of the Metrorail system until Palmetto station opened in 2003.

==Station layout==
The station has two tracks and an island platform, with parking underneath the tracks on either side of the station.

