<doc id="1051491" wikidata="Q5326523" url="?curid=1051491" title="Earlington Heights station">
<text>Earlington Heights station is a Metrorail station in the Liberty City neighborhood of Miami, Florida. This station is located at the intersection of Northwest 21st Avenue and the Airport Expressway (SR 112). The Metrorail Orange Line creation and extension of the metro to Miami International Airport (MIA) began construction from this rail station in May 2009, completed in July 2012. Passenger service between MIA, through Downtown Miami, and to the southern Miami suburb of Kendall opened in Summer 2012.

==Station layout==
The station has two tracks served by an island platform.

==Places of interest==
*Miami International Airport (via the Orange Line)
*Brownsville
*Allapattah
*Historic Miami Jackson High School
*Earlington Heights Elementary

