<doc id="1051615" wikidata="Q4878588" url="?curid=1051615" title="Beck's theorem">
<text>Beck&#x27;s theorem may refer to either of two mathematical results:
*Beck&#x27;s monadicity theorem or the Beck tripleability theorem (1964/2003), by Jonathan Mock Beck, on monadic functors in category theory 
*Beck&#x27;s theorem (geometry) (1983) by József Beck, on finite collections of points in discrete geometry </text><links>
